.TH GIT-PR-LAND-STACK 1 "2026-06-13" "git-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-pr-land-stack \- land a ready linear GitHub pull request stack
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git pr-land-stack
.RI [ options ]
.I number|url|branch
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git pr-land-stack
lands a linear stack of ready GitHub pull requests from parent to child.
It composes
.BR git-pr-stack (1),
.BR git-pr-land (1),
and
.BR git-pr-restack (1).
.PP
The command refuses the whole stack before merging anything if any pull request
is not ready. As each parent lands, the next child is restacked onto the root
base branch before it is landed.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-method " " \fImethod\fR
Merge method:
.BR squash ,
.BR merge ,
or
.BR rebase .
Defaults to
.BR squash .
.TP
.B \-\-keep\-branch
Pass
.B \-\-keep\-branch
to
.BR git-pr-land (1).
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-dry\-run
Print actions without changing anything.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Stack was landed.
.TP
.B 1
Stack is not ready or a child restack or merge failed.
.TP
.B 2
Usage or local environment error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-pr-ready (1),
.BR git-pr-stack (1),
.BR git-pr-restack (1),
.BR git-pr-land (1)
